OL,6,F"No note was even taken of anything
OL,7,Fthat was said. We now know he
OL,8,Fcontinued to offend. That's very
OL,9,Fconcerning indeed".
OL,11,FCeri Ellis-Jones, of the Crown
OL,12,FProsecution Service, said: "These
OL,13,Fcrimes were shocking as Foden was a
OL,14,Ftrusted and well-respected individual.
OL,16,F"The victims are to be commended for
OL,17,Ftheir bravery in coming forward and
OL,18,Fgiving evidence. Their support for
OL,19,Fthis prosecution has been key to Foden
OL,20,Fbeing brought to justice.
